locality: Yemen, gov. Hadhramout, Kor Seiban, wadi (running N to S) immediately W of the highest point, bottom and E facing slope.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. Jabal Fartak between Haswayn and Al Ghaida, SW-facing slopes of the mountain and plateau with the radio station. Succulent decumbent shrub. Alt.: 550-950 m. 26.11.1999, Leg.: P. Hein & N. Kilian PH 6860.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. Jabal Sharwayn 10 km W of Qeshn, rocky slopes and plateau looking on the Qeshn plain. Rocky slopes, strongly affected by the monsoonal mist: succulent rich Euphorbia balsamifera zone. Succulent plant. Alt.: 180 m. 24.9.1998, Leg.: P. Hein, S. A. Ghazanfar & N. Kilian PH 4887.

Yemen: Hadhramout. Jol plateau NW of Al Mukalla, Jol Seyban between Ras Huwayra (near the Seyun-Mukalla main road) and Bayn al Jib l. Alt.: 1820 m. 30.10.2000, Leg.: N. Kilian, S. O. Bahah, A. F. Bin Nesr, P. Hein & M. A. Hubaishan NK 6527.

Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. Jol plateau, on pipeline rd., 4.5 km SE of. Gravel flat on table mountain close to its SE exp. escarpment. Alt.: 1300 m. 17.9.2001, Leg.: N. Kilian, P. Hein & M. A. Hubaishan YP 117.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. Northern Fartak Mts, on the road from Hashwein to Al-Ghaida, wadi S of the pass crossing road. Alt.: 320 m. 8.10.2001, Leg.: N. Kilian, H. Kürschner & J. Meister YP 1122.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. north-eastern flank of the Ras Fartak SW of Nishtun, rocky slopes facing N/NE. Bare steep slopes with spare soil; no trees present, the shrubs all rather small. Common small shrubs, 10-20 cm tall, with succulent obovate greyish-green leaves, the flowers white. Alt.: 200-450 m. 20.11.1999, Leg.: P. Hein & N. Kilian PH 6588.

Yemen: Hadhramout. upper Wadi Fuwwah, here called Wadi Al Muhammedin, near the village As Safal. loamy ground. Alt.: 430-550 m. 30.11.1999, Leg.: N. Kilian, S. M. A. Bashmeilah, P. Hein & A. F. Bin Nesr NK 6451.

Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. Jol plateau, on the pipeline rd. from Wadi Araf to Tawila fields, near a huge water dam. Rocky slopes with scattered trees and shrubs, and stony plateau with low shrubby vegetation. Alt.: 1260 m. 18.9.2001, Leg.: N. Kilian, P. Hein & M. A. Hubaishan YP 209.
Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. road between Al Mukalla and the Wadi Hadhramout, on top of the Jol plateau. Alt.: 1500 m. 21.3.1996, Leg.: P. Hein & E. von Raab-Straube PH 311.

Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. Al Mukalla - Sayun main road, Jol plateau c 15 km SE of Huwayrah. Shrub, 50 cm tall, on rocky slopes. Alt.: 1250-1300 m. 10.11.1999, Leg.: P. Hein, M. Al-Mashjary & N. Kilian PH 6250.

Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. Jol, road from Seyun to Mukalla, 30 km N Ras Howeirah (20 km S Wadi Ayn). Depression in the otherwise stony plateau, with alluvial loamy and silty soil. Alt.: 1230 m. 18.10.2001, Leg.: N. Kilian, P. Hein & H. Kürschner YP 1303.

Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. middle Wadi Azid al Jabal c 25 km N of the town Qusayr (Kosair). Gravelly plain (diameter of the gravel 3-10 cm) at a gorge like narrow part of the wadi. Wadi vegetation with annuals and small herbsFlowers cream coloured. Alt.: 180 m. 20.11.2000, Leg.: P. Hein, S. O. Bahah, M. A. Hubaishan & N. Kilian PH 8308.
